    "Body": " Forecasting and Scheduling Analyst at Overstock.com Inc. Midvale, UT 84047 ?? About the Job Job Summary The Workforce Management Forecasting and Scheduling Analyst is responsible for forecasting long term, short term and intraday contact volume, determining headcount requirements, generating staffing schedules and analyzing a wide range of data to facilitate the smooth functioning of both the multi-channel in-house contact center and the third-party vendor.?? Job Responsibilities Create long term, short-term and interval-level contact volume forecasts derived from business drivers and historical data. Create staff schedules for multiple departments and adjust them to meet changing business needs. Maintain and analyze records of actual volumes compared to forecast. Maintain detailed records of call arrival patterns and statistics to maximize forecasting accuracy and ensure cost effective labor utilization. Maintain staffing and headcount records and develop hiring plans for long and short-range planning. Work closely with the Real-Time Analysts and other members of the Workforce Management Team to facilitate the smooth operation of the Customer Contact Center. Create other reports, as required, to assist in forecasting and operational planning, and to aid in decision-making. Perform other duties as required and assigned by manager and the Customer Service Leadership Team. Follow legal policies as directed. Job Requirements Two to four years of Workforce Management experience in a multi-channel contact center environment (real-time analysis, scheduling, forecasting, staffing, etc.), required. Two to three years of experience in a forecasting or analytical role within a medium to large volume, enterprise-level, multi-channel contact center or insurance or captive finance company, strongly preferred. Ability to manipulate and model data, create reports and work with relational database structures for Workforce Management forecasting, strongly preferred. Ability to work with Business Intelligence databases (i.e. SQL, SAS, Informix, Cognos) and obtain data from various sources, is a plus. Skills \u200bIntermediate to expert level proficiency in Microsoft Excel, including data analysis functions, pivot tables, charts and complex formulas, required. Intermediate data analysis skills and the ability interpret data to provide recommendations to drive key business decisions, required. Advanced working knowledge of Microsoft Office applications, required. Intermediate level proficiency with contact center platforms (e.g. InContact, Genesys, Cisco) and WFM tools (e.g. IEX, Aspect eWFM, Blue Pumpkin) for forecasting call volume, scheduling, reporting, etc., strongly preferred. Ability to work independently with minimal supervision and as a contributing team member. Ability to work on multiple projects simultaneously, and to adjust to changing priorities. Ability to communicate with discretion and professionalism, and to understand when confidentiality is required. Ability to interact and clearly communicate with all levels of management. Demonstrated complex problems solving skills. Strong organizational skills and a high level of attention to detail. Education \u200b High school diploma, GED or equivalent required.?? Bachelor's degree in Finance, Mathematics or Statistics strongly preferred, or equivalent work experience. Certifications Physical Requirements Equal Employment Opportunity It is our policy to provide equal employment opportunity for all applicants and associates.\u202f This policy includes our commitment to ensure that all employment decisions are made without regard to race, color, religion, gender, national origin, disability, pregnancy, veteran status (including Vietnam era veterans), age, sexual orientation, gender identity, or any other non-job-related characteristic protected by law.\u202f Who We Are: Just a few minutes from Salt Lake City and Utah\u2019s ski slopes, Overstock is an original resident of \u